 a cinematic podcast. It’s grown quickly and I’m not slowing down anytime soon.✔️ Personal Branding consulting: Growth, strategy, LinkedIn, content strategy, etc. I only work with 10 personal branding clients a year. 😊✔️ Speaking at your event: I’ve done talks at INBOUND, VidCon, TEDx, and more.✔️ Esports — one of my main passions is esports (and just gaming overall). I will be helping endemic & non-endemic brands via connections, sponsorships, and branding/personal branding.Feel free to reach out to me here, via email, or you can learn more about me on my website: quentinallums.com",7 months ago,"For me, 2016- (the start of) 2020 was an epic story: ✅ Quit my full-time job to start a company. ✅ First company failed. Burned through funds, had to rent out my extra rooms just to pay rent, power was turned off a few times. ✅ Recorded videos documenting my thought process through everything. ✅ Eventually people took notice of my videos. I helped a lot of people grow in the same way that I did. ✅ I was homeless for a handful of months. Slept on my office floor. Sometimes Airbnb's or hotels.  ✅ Launched a new company with a friend and two semi-strangers and we grew really quickly. Made a lot of mistakes. Make a lot of good decisions too.  ✅ Spoke on stages like VidCon, TEDx, and INBOUND. ✅ I can now be tied back to the inception of a lot of LinkedIn influencers. This year has not been ideal. It wasn't a part of my plan. At the beginning of the year I felt like I was about to jump on a launch pad into a new universe. Now it feels like the next chapter... maybe even a new book.  The more we linger on the old bullet points, the more we keep ourselves from creating new ones. I don't entirely know what the next chapter looks like. But I know it's going to be a good story. And that's all we really are anyway — stories. ""Let's just make it a good one, eh?"" #justQ  🖖🏽🖤 
 
 
