itution. He received his bachelor's degree in international relations from Tulane University.Ian established Eurasia Group with just $25,000 in 1998. Today, the company has offices in New York, Washington, San Francisco, London, Brasilia, Sao Paulo, Singapore, and Tokyo, as well as a network of experts and resources in 90 countries.",3 weeks ago,"Could the Russian cyberattack have been averted? Former Homeland Security Sec. Jeh Johnson wonders if Trump's decision to sack Chris Krebs (who headed the agency in charge of US cybersecurity) left the country vulnerable. #cybersecurity   #cyberpeace   #cyberattacks   #Russia   Watch  GZERO Media 's  #GZEROWorld : https://lnkd.in/dA4xsZ2 
 
 
